&quot;Two teenage boys were critically injured, and three others were rushed to several nearby medical facilities with serious injuries after a hand grenade detonated at a house in Goud Street, Vanguard Estate at around 19H00 last (on Monday) night ,&quot; said Robert Daniels the principal communications officer in a statement.&quot;Western Cape Government Health Emergency medical Services rushed the boys to Groote Schuur Hospital as well as a nearby private medical facility. Details surrounding the circumstances of the explosion are still unclear, but police are investigating.&quot;African News Agency